## Banned Vocabulary

These words are AI slop. They make output sound generated instead of written. Never use them.

### Banned Adjectives and Adverbs

| Word | Why it is banned |
|------|-----------------|
| delve | Nobody says this in conversation |
| crucial | Use "important" or just show why it matters |
| robust | Meaningless without specifics |
| comprehensive | Vague. Say what it covers. |
| nuanced | If it is nuanced, show the nuance |
| multifaceted | Corporate jargon |
| pivotal | Melodramatic |
| intricate | Show the complexity, do not label it |
| vibrant | Marketing speak |
| fundamental | Overused filler |
| significant | Be specific about the magnitude |
| innovative | Let the reader decide |
| cutting-edge | Dated buzzword |
| game-changing | Hyperbolic |
| best-in-class | Unprovable claim |
| holistic | Consultant speak |
| seamless | Nothing is seamless |
| scalable | Without numbers, meaningless |
| synergistic | Corporate fever dream |

### Banned Verbs

| Word | Use instead |
|------|------------|
| delve | dig into, look at, check |
| leverage | use |
| utilize | use |
| facilitate | help, enable, let |
| empower | give, let, enable |
| foster | build, create, grow |
| showcase | show, demonstrate |
| underscore | show, highlight |
| streamline | simplify, speed up |
| optimize | improve, speed up, reduce |
| spearhead | lead, start |
| revolutionize | change, improve |
| transform | change |

### Banned Adverbs and Transitions

| Word | Use instead |
|------|------------|
| furthermore | also, and |
| moreover | also, and |
| additionally | also, and |
| consequently | so |
| nevertheless | but, still |
| notwithstanding | despite |
| henceforth | from now on |
