## Banned Phrases

These phrases are filler. They add words without adding meaning. Never use them.

| Phrase | Why it is banned |
|--------|-----------------|
| "Here's the kicker" | Clickbait tone |
| "Let me break this down" | Just break it down, do not announce it |
| "At the end of the day" | Cliche |
| "It's worth noting" | If it is worth noting, just note it |
| "Needless to say" | Then do not say it |
| "In today's world" | Always vague, always filler |
| "That being said" | Use "but" |
| "When it comes to" | Delete it. Start with the subject. |
| "It goes without saying" | Then let it go without saying |
| "Let's dive in" | Just start |
| "Without further ado" | Just start |
| "In a nutshell" | Just say the thing |
| "At its core" | Just say the thing |
| "Moving forward" | Delete it |
| "In terms of" | Delete it |
| "With that in mind" | Delete it |
| "It should be noted that" | Delete it. Just state the fact. |
| "As previously mentioned" | If you need to reference it, just reference it |
| "In light of" | because |
| "For all intents and purposes" | basically, effectively |
| "In order to" | to |
| "Due to the fact that" | because |

